      </owl:ObjectProperty>
    </owl:inverseOf>
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://www.ontology.org.il/HebrewManuscripts/2025-12-06#Codicological_Unit"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.ontology.org.il/HebrewManuscripts/2025-12-06#Codicological_Unit"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">follows unit</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="he">עוקב ליחידה</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Links a codicological unit to the unit that follows it in order</rdfs:comment>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
  <owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="http://www.ontology.org.il/HebrewManuscripts/2025-12-06#paradigm_bridge">
    <rdfs:domain rdf:resource="http://www.ontology.org.il/HebrewManuscripts/2025-12-06#ParadigmBridge"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Thing"/>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="en">paradigm bridge</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:label xml:lang="he">גשר פרדיגמטי</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment xml:lang="en">Generic bridging property connecting entities across paradigms</rdfs:comment>
  </owl:ObjectProperty>
  <owl:Ontology rdf:about="http://www.ontology.org.il/HebrewManuscripts/2025-12-06">
    <owl:versionIRI rdf:resource="http://www.ontology.org.il/HebrewManuscripts/2025-12-06/1.8"/>
    <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://iflastandards.info/ns/lrm/lrmoo/1.0"/>
    <owl:imports rdf:resource="http://www.cidoc-crm.org/cidoc-crm/7.1.3"/>
    <dcterms:title xml:lang="en">Hebrew Manuscripts Ontology</dcterms:title>
    <dcterms:title xml:lang="he">אונטולוגיה לכתבי יד עבריים</dcterms:title>
    <dcterms:description xml:lang="en">An ontology for describing Hebrew manuscripts metadata based on LRMoo and CIDOC-CRM, developed for the National Library of Israel Linked Open Data project.

VERSION 1.4 - 100% Expert Feedback Coverage
============================================

This version addresses all expert feedback from Prof. Moshe Lavi, Dr. Eliezer Baumgarten, and Prof. Gila Prebor on the Hebrew manuscript ontology.

NEW FEATURES:

1. DUAL PARADIGM SUPPORT (Resolves Gila's philosophical tension)
   - CatalogingView: Bibliographic-practical approach using LRM Work-Expression model
   - PhilologicalView: New philology approach treating each MS as unique cultural event
   - ParadigmBridge: Explicit bridging between Work and TextTradition concepts
   - Manuscripts can exist in both paradigms simultaneously
   - Suitable for both Wikidata integration and philological research

2. NESTED CODICOLOGICAL STRUCTURE (Addresses Eliezer's hierarchy concern)
   - has_sub_unit: Transitive property enabling recursive CU nesting
   - CodicologicalHierarchy: Manages complex manuscript compositions
   - CompositeCodicologicalUnit: Parent units containing sub-divisions
   - AtomicCodicologicalUnit: Leaf-level units
   - Supports MTM (Multiple Text Manuscripts), Sammelbands, complex anthologies

3. EPISTEMOLOGICAL FRAMEWORK (Addresses Moshe's fact vs interpretation concern)
   - EpistemologicalStatus: DirectObservation, ScholarlyInterpretation, ComputationalDerivation
   - EvidenceChain: Documents reasoning paths from raw data to conclusions
   - EvidenceStep hierarchy: DirectObservationStep, InterpretationStep, ComputationalStep
   - InterpretationMethod: Paleographic, Codicological, Linguistic, AI-based analysis
   - DataCategory: Distinguishes physical measurements, attributions, relationships

PREVIOUSLY IMPLEMENTED (v1.1-1.3):
- Certainty/confidence mechanisms with categorical and percentage values
- Variant and partial identification relationships
- Textual overlap properties for overlapping scribal units
- Multi-volume and anthology structures
- Scribal intervention documentation
- Lost manuscript handling
- Full granularity support (folio to character level)
- Canonical hierarchy references (Bible, Mishnah, Talmud, Mishneh Torah, Shulchan Aruch)
- Foreign unit marking for non-core manuscript components
- Text Tradition layer for philological transmission analysis

EXPERT FEEDBACK TEST CASES ADDRESSED:
- Vat 44: Multi-volume mechanism (MultiVolumeSet, is_volume_of)
- Huntington 115: Overlapping scribal hands (has_textual_overlap_with)
- Oppenheimer 128: Rigid hierarchy (nested CU with has_sub_unit)
- Parma 3122: Anthology structure (AnthologyStructure, AnthologyPosition)
- London Sifrei Toviah: Marginalia relationships (Marginalia, has_marginalia)
- Jerusalem 8210: Foreign units (UnitStatusType, is_foreign_addition)
- London 9599: Lost manuscripts (LostManuscript, is_copy_of_lost)

USAGE NOTES:
- For cataloging purposes: Use CatalogingView with Work-Expression-Manifestation
- For philological research: Use PhilologicalView with TextTradition-TransmissionWitness
- For complex manuscripts: Use CodicologicalHierarchy with nested has_sub_unit
- For all assertions: Attach EpistemologicalStatus to distinguish facts from interpretations
- For AI-derived data: Use ComputationalDerivation status with AIBasedAnalysis method

VERSION 1.5 - Administrative &amp; Access Metadata (February 2026)
==============================================================

New classes: PhysicalHolding, DigitalAccess, UsageRestriction, RightsDetermination
New object properties: has_physical_holding, has_digital_access, has_usage_restriction, 
    has_rights_determination, has_related_material, held_at
New datatype properties: copyright_notice, related_material_note, acquisition_source,
    collection_name, restriction_type, restriction_url, rights_status, rights_basis,
    holding_institution, holding_sublibrary, holding_collection, holding_call_number,
    holding_availability, digital_access_url, digital_access_note, digital_access_type

These additions ensure complete coverage of all semantically meaningful MARC fields
from NLI records, including physical holdings (AVA), digital access (AVE), usage 
restrictions (939), rights determination (952), copyright (597), related materials 
(544), acquisition sources (541), and collection names (966).

VERSION 1.5.1 - Ontology Hygiene (February 2026)
==================================================

- Added named inverse hm:has_volume for hm:is_volume_of (replaces anonymous inverse in MultiVolumeSet restriction).
- Removed legacy hm:anthology_position datatype shortcut; canonical pattern: hm:has_anthology_position + hm:AnthologyPosition + hm:anthology_order.
- Added disjointness axioms: LostManuscript/AnthologyStructure, text-tradition classes, canonical reference subtypes.
- Documented Functional property semantics for is_volume_of.
- Clarified namespace policy (: vs hm: prefix).

VERSION 1.6 - Ontology Improvements (February 2026)
====================================================

- Documented anthology position: enhanced rdfs:comment on hm:has_anthology_position and hm:anthology_order.
- New inverse properties: hm:was_former_owner_of (inverse of hm:former_owner), hm:hosts_part (inverse of hm:is_part_of_host).
- Colophon: rdfs:comment clarifying that every Colophon must have at least one hm:colophon_text value.
- Disjointness: owl:AllDisjointClasses for E55_Type subclasses (ConditionType, VocalizationType, BindingType, etc.) and location classes (FolioLocation, LineLocation, WordLocation, CharacterLocation) already present.
- SHACL: minCount 1 for hm:external_identifier_nli (ManuscriptShape), hm:has_folio_range and hm:mentions_scribe (Warning), cidoc-crm:P4_has_time-span (Violation for production events).
- Breaking cleanup: removed legacy properties has_Script_Mode, external_wikidata_id, anthology_position, links_work_to_tradition, links_tradition_to_work; use canonical replacements only (see LEGACY_TO_CANONICAL_CHECKLIST.md).
- CIDOC-CRM: added E26_Physical_Feature class declaration (superclass of hm:Watermark).

VERSION 1.7 - Structural &amp; Semantic Fixes (February 2026)
===========================================================

- R69_has_physical_form: domain changed from comma-intersection to owl:unionOf (F3_Manifestation OR F4_Manifestation_Singleton).
- Added lrmoo:R3i_realises as inverse of R3_is_realised_in; SHACL ExpressionShape and ExpressionWorkRule now use R3i_realises.
- hm:P44_has_condition: range narrowed from cidoc-crm:E55_Type to hm:ConditionType to match SHACL and usage.
- SHACL ProductionEventShape: replaced full IRIs with lrmoo: prefixed names (F32_Item_Production_Event, R27_materialized) so shape targets correct class.

VERSION 1.8 - Ontology Hygiene &amp; SHACL (February 2026)
=========================================================

- Legacy aliases removed (breaking); canonical terms only.
- Removed redundant standalone owl:disjointWith for CatalogingView/PhilologicalView (kept AllDisjointClasses).
- Unified symmetric property syntax: rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty , owl:SymmetricProperty for parallels, has_textual_overlap_with, is_paradigm_compatible, adjacent_unit, competing_interpretation.
- Removed redundant rdfs:domain owl:Thing from 14 properties (has_certainty, attribution_source, attributed_by, has_location, external_identifier_nli, external_uri_nli, external_wikidata_uri, wikidata_id, certainty_percentage, certainty_note, has_epistemological_status, has_evidence_chain, data_category, is_factual).
- SHACL: added EvidenceChainShape, ParadigmBridgeShape, CompositeCodicologicalUnitShape, ManuscriptViewShape.

REASONING NOTES:
- This ontology is designed to be used with OWL-DL reasoners (e.g. Pellet, HermiT).
- Functional, Inverse, Transitive, and Asymmetric property characteristics are declared where appropriate.
- AllDisjointClasses and AllDifferent axioms enable reasoners to detect classification errors.
- For data validation beyond OWA entailment, use the companion SHACL shapes (shacl-shapes.ttl).</dcterms:description>
    <dcterms:creator>Alexander Goldberg</dcterms:creator>
    <dcterms:contributor>Prof. Gila Prebor</dcterms:contributor>
    <dcterms:contributor>Prof. Moshe Lavi</dcterms:contributor>
    <dcterms:contributor>Dr. Eliezer Baumgarten</dcterms:contributor>
    <dcterms:created rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2025-12-06</dcterms:created>
    <dcterms:modified rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#date">2026-02-06</dcterms:modified>
    <owl:versionInfo>1.9 - Query compatibility and LOD alignment with canonical + bridge properties; MARC-only external identifier policy retained; ontology hygiene fixes preserved from 1.8.</owl:versionInfo>
